messages.content:
@everyone --This is not interactive. Please just sit back and enjoy--

*While blacked out, everyone has vivid dreams.  There is one key similarity to each dream - the inability to control your actions*

*The first dream:  Each character is in a band, playing to tens of thousands in an outdoor arena.  Each character is placed in a role with which they are uniquely uncomfortable.  If they can sing, they are tasked with drumming.  The drumset has over 15 pieces and contains items they've never seen before.  They must navigate it to create a solid rhythm for the band.  They fail, repeatedly.*

*If they are not comfortable singing, they are in the role of the lead singer of the band.  The rest of the band members play heavy metal music and they have no idea what any of the lyrics are. They struggle through and are booed*

*Louz is not placed as a member of the band.  He is sitting on a stool in the wings, forced to watch as a band made of his teammates butchers every one of his songs, in front of a crowd of tens of thousands.*
((Antoni, who would be equally uncomfortable in either position: Why am I in 2 places at once?
((Oh Pulse would hate every *minute* of this
*Antoni is playing the drums with a mic to sing.  He's in the front of the stage, everyone else fades behind him*
((Dang it, I can't stop laughing picturing this XD
((I'm just happy that the drum set has *lots* of cow bell
((There's like 6 of them over there and it makes me happy

((I'd like to imagine that Pulse finds herself playing a guitar with way too many strings. She knows her fingers should be dexterous enough for this (especially the cyberarm) but she can't seem to get them to cooperate and now she's scared that she's not as steady as she thought she was. Maybe the stress is finally getting to her.
((Antoni: I have never touched an instrument in my life and I'm tonedeaf, WHYYYYYYY
((~~or maybe her stability was in her imagination~~
((If it were irl me tho, I'd 100% be the singer in my little nightmare (I am vaguely comfortable with an instrument but could not sing to save my life)
(Nice thing to see going off to camp
((Dude if it were irl me, I'd still be watching the train wreck XD
(And I’m literally stuck with 6th graders on a cramped bus
(OKAY BUT I GOT A SERVICE PROJECT OUT OF THE WAY
((You could do the same thing at a soup kitchen XD

@everyone 

*The second dream:*
*The characters relive the deaths of each person who was close to them.  From Finn's dog to Lex's dad, to their parents if they're dead.  Pulse relives every patient who died in her care.  Even the death of Cypher, if that mattered to them.*

*Except that this time, the deaths were specifically their fault, and they cannot do anything to stop it.  Finn's dog dies from a negligent discharge from his own firearm.  Lex's dad dies because he was working on the van she broke and he got shot.  And on, and on.*

*And there's nothing they can do about it.*
((Time to reread my backstory to see how this ends up affecting Antoni
((Huh. I surprisingly didn't fill his backstory with dead people
((That's an odd one for me lmao
((The dice gave Pulse a sad backstory and her career just added to it
((Yeah, the dice gave me the family tragedy of his family being forced into hiding, so no dead parents, and one of his friends being killed by an estranged relative
((Antoni has it better than most of the characters I've written would have in this scenario lol

*The third dream:*
*The characters have begun to realize that they are in a dream.  This one is different - they are playing a high-stakes card game that they do not recognize in a place that seems alien to them.  They are surrounded by strange-looking people.  In this case, their own life is on the line.  A thin wire encircles their neck, and as they lose the wire tightens more and more.  As the dream progresses, they begin to try to take control of the dream.  How well they do depends on their willpower:*

*For characters with 3 or less Will - they consistently make bad plays and understand the game less and less as time goes on.  The dream ends as blackness pulls in from the edges of their vision, laughter from their strange companions filling their ears.*

*For characters with 4-5 Will - they believe they are learning the game as it progresses.  They start trying to make intelligent plays that will turn the game around, but every time they try to do so they accidentally play a different card that loses them points.  The dream ends in much the same way it does for the previous set of characters.*

*For characters with 6-7 Will - they get the gist of the game relatively quickly.  They are able to begin playing cards with powerful effects, overtaking the game.  Over time, the alien beings around them quiet down and are much less jovial.  The character wins the game, and one of their opponents shoots them in the head in a fit of rage.*
((I will head canon that Antoni was losing a Yu-Gi-Oh duel because that sounds hilarious to me
I have a 4 willpower, so I lost the card game lmao))
(Same. Also feeling cute, might make a MedTech backup
((but yeah, I am headcanoning that Antoni got stuck playing Yu-Gi-Oh lmao
((especially since the Yu-Gi-Oh anime turns the card game into a death game A LOT XD
((then losing the duel 5 minutes later lmao

*The fourth dream:*

*Your character is in a white room with a white floor, white walls, and a white ceiling.  If they try to find out, they'll learn that they can't actually tell how large the room is.  If they walk, they never find the end.  After what feels like at least 15 minutes of exploring (or not, their choice), they suddenly feel a strong wind.  If they look in the direction of the wind, they'll see a black dot getting larger and larger.  All of a sudden, an entire city flies past them, just as suddenly stopping with them in the middle of a school playground.*

*They have a Matrix-like experience.  For what feels like 30 minutes, they are able to explore the environment and learn that they have far more control over both themselves and the environment than they should.  Higher Willpower characters will find that they can fly and change the materials of objects at will.  Even lower Willpower characters are able to move far faster than they should be able to and jump much higher.  These are only examples - the characters' limits are few.*

*After the 30 minutes, your character suddenly ends up in a dojo, with no explanation, and is treated to this scene from the Matrix (https://youtube.com/clip/Ugkx3tSpu_wYugksFNNCERovpbYk1WrE22bv), and they find that they are never fast enough or strong enough to beat the simulation.  the simulation ends with them on the floor, beaten.*
((Every time I think "Oh, this isn't so bad" Pulse ends up getting beaten down again

((Poor Pulse is going to wake up so unsettled. I would figure her reaction would be worse if she had no resist torture/drugs, but this still probably isn't fun and I'm not sure her number is high enough to even make much of a difference
(Case got nothing and was drunk, they’re gonna have a hard time

((Antoni at first: I know Judo, I might have a chance 
Antoni 5 minutes later: *proceeds to get his butt kicked in more ways than he can count*
((Antoni: I didn't even know one could kick butt like that-
((Meanwhile, Pulse: *tries for a minute* Ah. I see. Hm. Don't seem to be winning this one. *gets slammed into floor*

@everyone

*The final dream:*

*Your character opens their eyes to find themselves hanging upside-down from seatbelts in a vehicle appears to have been in a bad accident.  They are in the driver's seat.  There is blood in their eyes and their hair and they cannot move their right arm.  They can move their legs, but cannot feel them.  The windshield is shattered, the steering wheel broken, and the interior is in general disarray.  *

*If they look toward the passenger seat they will find another of the team hanging there, dead from a metal shard that has run through their chest.  For Pulse, it's Louz, for Louz it's Lex, for Lex it's Case, for Case it's Antoni, for Antoni it's Finn, for Finn it's Pulse.*

*They are able to struggle to get out of the vehicle, and once they do so, it slides on it's roof into a fast-flowing river that is just beside them.  They have narrowly escaped drowning.  The character quickly realizes that they need medical help and attempt to find a hospital.  Those with a Perception Base of 10 or more realize that they are in a town not at all like Night City.  There are no trappings of Cyberpunk life in this small, midwestern town - no neon signs, no LED paint glowing to mark the crosswalks and other road markings, no flying vehicles of any kind, etc.  Those with a Perception Base below 10 are in this same town, but don't realize that it's not Night City.*

*Depending on how well the character has done with controlling the environment in past dreams, they realize that they have control over this one.  Some are able to create feeling in their legs again.  Some even find a way to fly.  They are able, in many ways, to affect their world and themselves, but they are never able to heal themselves.  One way or another, they each end up at a hospital emergency ward and collapse in front of the desk, blacking out.*
(Case saw you bro they’re literally so upset
